(44, 6, 2, 16, 6, 3, 3, 'the word of God', 'Commitment to Important Work', 'This connection highlights the prioritization of significant tasks over lesser duties. Both passages emphasize the necessity of focusing on essential work rather than being distracted by other responsibilities.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 2, 4, 11, 11, 13, 'serve tables', 'Burden of Leadership', 'This connection highlights the theme of leadership burdens. Both Moses and the apostles express concern about the demands placed on them, indicating the struggle to balance spiritual responsibilities with practical needs.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 2, 44, 25, 27, 27, 'not reason', 'Reasonableness in Decision Making', 'This connection highlights the theme of reasonableness in decision-making. Both passages emphasize what is deemed ''unreasonable'' in their respective contexts, reflecting the importance of proper prioritization and justification in actions.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 2, 44, 4, 19, 19, 'the word of God', 'Authority of God vs. Service', 'This connection highlights the prioritization of divine authority over earthly responsibilities. Both passages emphasize the necessity of focusing on God''s word rather than being distracted by other duties.', 'theme', 0.3, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 3, 54, 3, 7, 15, 'honest report', 'Qualifications for Church Leaders', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of having men of ''honest report'' and good character in leadership roles within the church. Acts 6:3 outlines the selection of leaders based on their integrity and wisdom, while 1 Timothy 3:7-15 provides further qualifications for deacons, highlighting the need for a good reputation and moral conduct.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 3, 5, 1, 13, 13, 'full of the Holy Ghost and wisdom', 'Wisdom and Leadership in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the selection of wise individuals for leadership roles. Acts 6:3 calls for men ''full of the Holy Ghost and wisdom,'' while Deuteronomy 1:13 instructs to ''take you wise men'' for rulership.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 3, 59, 3, 17, 18, 'full of the Holy Ghost and wisdom', 'Wisdom and Righteousness Connection', 'This connection highlights the importance of wisdom in both passages. Acts 6:3 emphasizes selecting men ''full of the Holy Ghost and wisdom,'' while James 3:17 describes wisdom as ''full of mercy and good fruits,'' linking the qualities of wisdom to righteous actions.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 3, 4, 27, 18, 19, 'full of the Holy Ghost', 'Leadership and Spiritual Qualification', 'Both passages emphasize the selection of leaders who are filled with the Spirit. Acts 6:3 mentions men ''full of the Holy Ghost,'' while Numbers 27:18 refers to Joshua as ''a man in whom is the spirit.'' This connection highlights the importance of spiritual qualifications in leadership roles.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 3, 54, 5, 10, 10, 'honest report', 'Qualifications for Service', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of being ''well reported of'' and having a good reputation in the community. Acts 6:3 focuses on selecting men of honest report, while 1 Timothy 5:10 highlights good works as a measure of a woman''s reputation.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 3, 44, 13, 2, 3, 'full of the Holy Ghost', 'Connection of Holy Spirit and Leadership', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the Holy Ghost in guiding leadership decisions within the early church. In Acts 6:3, the selection of leaders is based on being ''full of the Holy Ghost,'' while Acts 13:2-3 shows the Holy Ghost directing the calling of Barnabas and Saul.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 3, 1, 41, 38, 39, 'full of the Holy Ghost and wisdom', 'Wisdom and the Spirit of God', 'This connection highlights the emphasis on being ''full of the Holy Ghost and wisdom'' in Acts, paralleling Pharaoh''s recognition of Joseph as ''discreet and wise'' in Genesis. Both passages underscore the importance of divine wisdom and the Spirit of God in leadership roles.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 4, 44, 1, 14, 14, 'prayer', 'Prayer and Ministry Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of prayer within the early church community. Acts 6:4 highlights the commitment to prayer alongside ministry, while Acts 1:14 shows the collective devotion to prayer among the believers.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 4, 54, 4, 13, 16, 'ministry of the word', 'Ministry and Doctrine Emphasis', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of ministry and doctrine. Acts 6:4 highlights dedication to prayer and the ministry of the word, while 1 Timothy 4:13-16 encourages attention to reading, exhortation, and doctrine.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 4, 50, 1, 9, 11, 'prayer', 'Prayer and Righteousness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of prayer and spiritual growth. Acts 6:4 highlights prayer and ministry, while Philippians 1:9-11 focuses on love and righteousness, suggesting a link between prayerful devotion and the fruits of righteousness.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 4, 44, 2, 42, 42, 'to prayer', 'Prayer and Ministry Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of prayer in the early church. Acts 6:4 highlights the commitment to prayer and ministry, while Acts 2:42 mentions prayers as a key practice of the believers.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 4, 55, 4, 2, 2, 'ministry of the word', 'Connection of Ministry and Preaching', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of the ministry of the word. Acts 6:4 highlights dedication to prayer and the ministry, while 2 Timothy 4:2 focuses on preaching the word with diligence.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 4, 45, 1, 9, 9, 'prayer, and to the ministry of the word', 'Prayer and Ministry Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of prayer in the context of ministry. Acts 6:4 highlights a commitment to prayer and the ministry of the word, while Romans 1:9 reflects a personal dedication to prayer in service to the gospel.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 4, 49, 3, 14, 21, 'prayer', 'Prayer and Spiritual Strength', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of prayer and spiritual empowerment. Acts 6:4 highlights dedication to prayer, while Ephesians 3:16 speaks of being strengthened by the Spirit.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 5, 44, 11, 24, 24, 'full of faith and of the Holy Ghost', 'Connection of Faith and the Holy Ghost', 'Both passages emphasize being ''full of the Holy Ghost and of faith.'' This connection highlights the importance of these qualities in the early church and their role in attracting others to the faith.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 5, 44, 21, 8, 8, 'Philip, and Prochorus, and Nicanor', 'Connection of Philip the Evangelist', 'Both passages emphasize Philip''s role in the early church. In Acts 6:5, he is chosen as one of the seven, and in Acts 21:8, he is identified as Philip the evangelist, linking his ministry across the narrative.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 5, 20, 15, 23, 23, NULL, 'Joy in Wise Choices', 'This connection highlights the joy that comes from making wise decisions, as seen in Acts 6:5 where the community chooses Stephen and others, reflecting the good outcome of their choice. Proverbs 15:23 emphasizes the joy of timely words, suggesting that both passages celebrate the positive results of thoughtful actions and decisions.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 5, 1, 41, 37, 37, 'the saying pleased the whole multitude', 'Agreement Among Leaders', 'This connection highlights the approval of a decision by a group. Both passages emphasize the positive reception of choices made by leaders and their followers.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 5, 20, 15, 1, 1, 'full of faith and of the Holy Ghost', 'Connection of Response and Leadership', 'This connection highlights the importance of a calm and measured response in leadership, as seen in Stephen''s selection for his faith and character. Proverbs emphasizes that a soft answer can diffuse anger, paralleling the qualities needed in those chosen to lead.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 5, 33, 3, 8, 8, 'full of faith and of the Holy Ghost', 'Connection of Spiritual Empowerment', 'Both passages emphasize being ''full of'' the Spirit, highlighting the importance of divine empowerment for ministry and proclamation. Stephen is described as ''full of faith and of the Holy Ghost,'' while Micah speaks of being ''full of power by the spirit of the Lord.''', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 5, 40, 23, 15, 15, 'a proselyte of Antioch', 'Connection of Proselytes in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of proselytes, highlighting the contrasting views on their significance. Acts 6:5 mentions Nicolas, a proselyte, while Matthew 23:15 critiques the Pharisees'' approach to making proselytes.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 6, 4, 8, 10, 10, 'laid their hands on them', 'Connection of Laying on Hands', 'This connection highlights the act of laying hands as a means of consecration and commissioning. Both passages emphasize the communal involvement in setting apart individuals for service.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 6, 55, 1, 6, 6, 'laid their hands on them', 'Connection of Laying on Hands', 'This connection highlights the act of laying hands as a means of imparting spiritual gifts. Both passages emphasize the significance of this practice in the early church.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 6, 44, 1, 24, 24, 'and when they had prayed', 'Prayer and Divine Guidance', 'Both passages emphasize the act of prayer as a means of seeking divine guidance. In Acts 1:24, the apostles pray for God''s choice, while in Acts 6:6, prayer precedes the laying on of hands, indicating reliance on God''s direction.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 6, 44, 8, 17, 17, 'laid their hands on them', 'Connection of Laying on Hands', 'Both passages emphasize the act of laying hands as a means of imparting spiritual authority and blessings. In Acts 6:6, the apostles lay hands on chosen individuals, while in Acts 8:17, they lay hands to confer the Holy Spirit.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 6, 54, 4, 14, 14, NULL, 'Connection of Laying on Hands', 'Both passages emphasize the act of laying on of hands as a significant ritual in the context of imparting gifts or authority. Acts 6:6 describes the apostles laying hands on chosen individuals, while 1 Timothy 4:14 refers to a similar practice associated with the gift given through prophecy.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 6, 54, 5, 22, 22, 'laid their hands on them', 'Connection of Laying on Hands', 'Both passages emphasize the act of laying hands, indicating a significant practice in the early church. Acts 6:6 shows the apostles laying hands on chosen individuals, while 1 Timothy 5:22 warns against doing so hastily, highlighting the importance of discernment in this practice.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 6, 58, 6, 2, 2, NULL, 'Connection of Laying on of Hands', 'This connection highlights the practice of laying on of hands as a significant act in both passages. Acts 6:6 describes the apostles laying hands on chosen individuals, while Hebrews 6:2 includes it as a foundational doctrine.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 7, 44, 19, 20, 20, 'the word of God increased', 'Growth of the Word of God', 'Both passages emphasize the growth and prevalence of the word of God within the community of believers. Acts 6:7 notes the increase of the word and disciples, while Acts 19:20 highlights its might and prevailing nature.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 7, 44, 12, 24, 24, 'the word of God increased', 'Growth of the Word of God', 'Both passages emphasize the growth of the word of God and its impact on the community. The phrase ''the word of God increased'' in Acts 6:7 parallels ''the word of God grew'' in Acts 12:24, highlighting a consistent theme of expansion.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 7, 51, 1, 6, 6, 'the word of God increased', 'Growth of Disciples and Fruitfulness', 'This connection highlights the theme of growth in the faith community. Both passages emphasize the increase of disciples and the fruitfulness of the word of God.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 7, 58, 5, 9, 9, 'obedient to the faith', 'Obedience to the Faith', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of obedience. Acts 6:7 mentions a great company of priests being ''obedient to the faith,'' while Hebrews 5:9 states that eternal salvation is for those who ''obey him.'' This connection highlights the theme of obedience in the context of faith and salvation.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 7, 45, 1, 5, 5, 'obedient to the faith', 'Obedience to the Faith', 'This connection highlights the theme of ''obedience to the faith'' present in both passages. Acts 6:7 mentions a great company of priests being obedient to the faith, while Romans 1:5 speaks of obedience to the faith among all nations.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 7, 45, 16, 26, 26, 'obedient to the faith', 'Obedience of Faith Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of ''obedience to the faith'' present in both passages. Acts 6:7 mentions a ''great company of the priests were obedient to the faith,'' while Romans 16:26 refers to ''the obedience of faith'' made known to all nations.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 7, 19, 132, 16, 16, 'a great company of the priests were obedient to the faith', 'Connection of Priests and Salvation', 'Both passages emphasize the obedience of priests and their relationship to faith and salvation. Acts 6:7 mentions a great company of priests being obedient to the faith, while Psalms 132:16 speaks of clothing priests with salvation.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 8, 44, 4, 29, 30, 'great wonders and miracles', 'Connection of Signs and Wonders', 'Both passages emphasize the performance of ''wonders and miracles'' as a manifestation of faith and divine power. Stephen''s acts in Acts 6:8 reflect the prayer for boldness and healing in Acts 4:29-30, showcasing the continuation of miraculous works in the early church.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 8, 44, 6, 5, 5, 'full of faith', 'Stephen''s Character and Actions', 'Both passages emphasize Stephen as a man full of faith. The first passage highlights his actions of performing wonders and miracles, which stem from his faith and empowerment by the Holy Spirit mentioned in the second passage.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 8, 54, 3, 13, 13, 'full of faith', 'Faith and Boldness in Service', 'This connection highlights the theme of faith and boldness in service to God. Stephen''s acts of power and miracles demonstrate the effectiveness of faith, while the reference to deacons in 1 Timothy emphasizes the importance of boldness in faith as a reward for their service.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 8, 43, 4, 48, 48, NULL, 'Connection of Signs and Wonders', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of signs and wonders in faith. Stephen''s miracles demonstrate the power that Jesus mentions as necessary for belief.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 8, 49, 4, 11, 11, 'full of faith and power', 'Spiritual Gifts and Ministry Roles', 'This connection highlights the empowerment of individuals in ministry. Stephen, described as ''full of faith and power,'' exemplifies the active role of believers, similar to the various ministry roles outlined in Ephesians.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 9, 40, 27, 32, 32, 'Cyrenians', 'Connection of Cyrene in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of Cyrene, linking the community of Cyrenians disputing with Stephen to Simon of Cyrene bearing the cross. This connection highlights the geographical and cultural significance of Cyrene in the early Christian narrative.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 9, 44, 15, 23, 23, 'Cilicia', 'Cilicia''s Role in Early Church', 'Both passages emphasize Cilicia as a significant region. In Acts 6:9, Cilicia is mentioned in the context of Stephen''s disputes, while Acts 15:23 highlights Cilicia as a destination for the apostles'' letters to the Gentiles.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
