(44, 6, 9, 40, 10, 17, 17, NULL, 'Persecution in Synagogues', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of persecution faced by believers in synagogues. Acts 6:9 describes Stephen''s disputes in a synagogue, while Matthew 10:17 warns of being delivered to councils and scourged in synagogues.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 9, 41, 13, 9, 9, NULL, 'Persecution in Synagogues', 'This connection highlights the theme of persecution faced by believers in synagogues. Both passages emphasize the conflict and disputes that arise in these religious settings, particularly against Stephen in Acts and the warnings given by Jesus in Mark.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 9, 42, 21, 12, 12, 'synagogue', 'Persecution and Synagogues', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of persecution faced by believers in synagogues. Acts 6:9 mentions disputing in the synagogue, while Luke 21:12 speaks of being delivered up to synagogues.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 9, 48, 1, 21, 21, 'Cilicia', 'Connection Between Stephen and Cilicia', 'This connection highlights the geographical link between Cilicia, mentioned in both passages. Stephen''s disputation in Acts involves individuals from Cilicia, while Galatians references Paul''s journey to the same region.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 10, 42, 21, 15, 15, 'not able to resist the wisdom', 'Wisdom and Resistance Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the inability of adversaries to resist wisdom. Acts 6:10 describes Stephen''s wisdom, while Luke 21:15 promises wisdom that opponents cannot gainsay.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 10, 40, 10, 19, 20, 'the spirit by which he spake', 'Wisdom and Spirit in Speech', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the Spirit in guiding speech. Acts 6:10 notes that the wisdom and spirit were unresistible, while Matthew 10:19-20 assures that the Spirit will provide words in moments of need.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 10, 46, 2, 4, 4, 'wisdom and the spirit', 'Wisdom and Spirit in Speech', 'Both passages emphasize the role of wisdom and the Spirit in effective communication. Acts 6:10 highlights the inability to resist the wisdom and spirit of Stephen, while 1 Corinthians 2:4 contrasts human wisdom with the demonstration of the Spirit and power in preaching.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 10, 43, 7, 46, 46, 'wisdom and the spirit by which he spake', 'Wisdom in Speech', 'This connection highlights the extraordinary nature of speech in both passages. Acts 6:10 notes the inability to resist the wisdom of Stephen, while John 7:46 emphasizes the uniqueness of Jesus'' words.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 10, 18, 32, 8, 8, 'the spirit by which he spake', 'Wisdom and Spirit Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the spirit in providing understanding and wisdom. Acts 6:10 highlights the wisdom and spirit of Stephen, while Job 32:8 speaks of the spirit in man that grants understanding.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 10, 42, 12, 11, 12, 'the wisdom and the spirit', 'Wisdom and the Holy Spirit', 'This connection highlights the role of the Holy Spirit in providing wisdom and guidance in speaking. Both passages emphasize that the wisdom and spirit enable effective communication in challenging situations.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 10, 2, 4, 12, 12, 'wisdom and the spirit by which he spake', 'Divine Guidance in Speech', 'Both passages emphasize divine assistance in speaking. Acts 6:10 highlights wisdom and spirit in speech, while Exodus 4:12 promises Godâ€™s presence to guide what to say.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 11, 40, 26, 59, 60, 'We have heard him speak blasphemous words', 'False Witness Against Leaders', 'This connection highlights the theme of false testimony against key figures in both passages. In Acts, false accusations are made against Stephen, while in Matthew, the council seeks false witnesses against Jesus.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 11, 11, 21, 10, 13, 'blasphemous words against Moses, and against God', 'Accusations of Blasphemy', 'Both passages emphasize false accusations of blasphemy against individuals. In Acts, Stephen is accused of speaking blasphemous words against Moses and God, while in 1 Kings, Naboth is falsely accused of blaspheming God and the king.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 11, 40, 28, 12, 15, 'blasphemous words against Moses, and against God', 'Accusations of Blasphemy', 'This connection highlights the theme of false accusations against key figures in the early church. In both passages, individuals are portrayed as fabricating claims to undermine the credibility of those who follow Jesus and Moses.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 11, 43, 1, 17, 17, 'against Moses', 'Law and Grace Contrast', 'This connection highlights the contrast between the law given by Moses and the grace brought by Jesus Christ. The accusation of blasphemy against Moses in Acts reflects the tension between adherence to the law and the new covenant of grace introduced by Christ.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 11, 43, 5, 45, 47, 'blasphemous words against Moses', 'Accusation Against Moses', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of accusation involving Moses. In Acts, false witnesses claim blasphemy against Moses, while in John, Jesus points to Moses as an accuser for those who do not believe. This connection highlights the role of Moses in the context of belief and accusation.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 11, 44, 6, 13, 13, 'blasphemous words', 'Blasphemy Accusations Against Stephen', 'This connection highlights the theme of blasphemy as both passages accuse Stephen of speaking against sacred figures and places. The phrase ''blasphemous words'' appears in both instances, linking the charges against him.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 11, 44, 7, 37, 39, 'blasphemous words against Moses', 'Connection Between Moses and Blasphemy', 'This connection highlights the accusation of blasphemy against Moses in Acts 6:11, which is addressed in Acts 7:37-39 by affirming Moses'' prophetic role. Both passages emphasize the significance of Moses in relation to God''s message and the people''s rejection of him.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 12, 20, 15, 18, 18, 'stirred up the people', 'Strife and Anger Connection', 'This connection highlights how both passages address the theme of strife. Acts 6:12 describes how people were stirred up, leading to conflict, while Proverbs 15:18 contrasts a wrathful man who stirs up strife with one who is slow to anger and appeases it.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 12, 44, 14, 2, 2, 'stirred up the people', 'Stirring Up the People', 'Both passages emphasize the act of stirring up opposition against believers. In Acts 6:12, the people are stirred up against Stephen, while in Acts 14:2, the unbelieving Jews stir up the Gentiles against the brethren.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
